---
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
import '../styles/Beep.css';
---
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Motherboard Beep Codes - DOST STII</title>
</head>
<body>
  <Header />

  <div class="beep-wrapper">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="beep-hero">
      <div class="beep-hero-icon">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16">
          <path d="M11.5 2a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5v7a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0v-7a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5m2 0a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5v7a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0v-7a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5m-10 8a.5.5 0 0 0 0 1h6a.5.5 0 0 0 0-1zm0 2a.5.5 0 0 0 0 1h6a.5.5 0 0 0 0-1zM5 3a1 1 0 0 0-1 1v4a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h4a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V4a1 1 0 0 0-1-1zm0 1h4v4H5z"/>
          <path d="M0 2a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h12a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v12a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H2a2 2 0 0 1-2-2zm2-1a1 1 0 0 0-1 1v12a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h12a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V2a1 1 0 0 0-1-1z"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h1 class="beep-hero-title">Motherboard Beep Code Reference</h1>
        <p class="beep-hero-sub">Diagnose hardware failures using POST (Power-On Self Test) audio signals</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro Section -->
    <section class="beep-section">
      <h2 class="beep-heading">What are BIOS Beep Codes?</h2>
      <p>When you turn on a computer, the motherboard performs a procedure called <strong>POST (Power-On Self Test)</strong>, which checks if all essential components are working properly. If a problem is found during this initial verification, the motherboard emits a series of sounds (BEEPs) through the internal speaker.</p>
      <p class="beep-highlight-text">These sounds are not random! They follow specific patterns that indicate which component has a problem. Each BIOS (Basic Input/Output System) manufacturer has its own set of sound codes.</p>

      <div class="beep-callout">
        <strong>Important:</strong> BEEP codes are the first diagnostic tool when a computer cannot complete the boot process to the point of displaying error messages on the screen.
      </div>

      <div class="beep-tags">
        <span class="beep-tag">BIOS</span>
        <span class="beep-tag">POST</span>
        <span class="beep-tag">Diagnostics</span>
        <span class="beep-tag">Hardware</span>
        <span class="beep-tag">Troubleshooting</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="beep-divider">

    <!-- Why Important -->
    <section class="beep-section">
      <h2 class="beep-heading">Why BEEP Codes are Important</h2>
      <p>BEEP codes are especially useful in the following scenarios:</p>
      <ul class="beep-list">
        <li>The computer cannot fully boot</li>
        <li>There is no display on the screen to show error messages</li>
        <li>You need to diagnose hardware problems quickly</li>
        <li>You are performing maintenance on multiple computers</li>
        <li>A component fails silently without any visible indication</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="beep-components">
        <div class="beep-component-card">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M5 0a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5V2h1V.5a.5.5 0 0 1 1 0V2h1V.5a.5.5 0 0 1 1 0V2h1V.5a.5.5 0 0 1 1 0V2A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 14 4.5h1.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1H14v1h1.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1H14v1h1.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1H14v1h1.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1H14a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-2.5 2.5v1.5a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0V14h-1v1.5a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0V14h-1v1.5a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0V14h-1v1.5a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0V14A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 2 11.5H.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0-1H2v-1H.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0-1H2v-1H.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0-1H2v-1H.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0-1H2A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4.5 2V.5A.5.5 0 0 1 5 0m-.5 3A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 3 4.5v7A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 4.5 13h7a1.5 1.5 0 0 0 1.5-1.5v-7A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 11.5 3zM5 6.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 6.5 5h3A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 11 6.5v3A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 9.5 11h-3A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 5 9.5zM6.5 6a.5.5 0 0 0-.5.5v3a.5.5 0 0 0 .5.5h3a.5.5 0 0 0 .5-.5v-3a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5z"/></svg>
          <span>CPU</span>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-component-card">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M4 0a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v1H1a1 1 0 0 0 0 2h1v2H1a1 1 0 0 0 0 2h1v2H1a1 1 0 0 0 0 2h1v1a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h8a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-1h1a1 1 0 0 0 0-2h-1V9h1a1 1 0 0 0 0-2h-1V5h1a1 1 0 0 0 0-2h-1V2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2zm0 1h8a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v12a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H4a1 1 0 0 1-1-1V2a1 1 0 0 1 1-1"/></svg>
          <span>RAM</span>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-component-card">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M4 8a1.5 1.5 0 1 1 3 0 1.5 1.5 0 0 1-3 0m7.5-1.5a1.5 1.5 0 1 0 0 3 1.5 1.5 0 0 0 0-3"/><path d="M0 1.5A.5.5 0 0 1 .5 1h1a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5V4h13.5a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5v7a.5.5 0 0 1-.5.5H2v2.5a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0V2H.5a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5m5.5 4a2.5 2.5 0 1 0 0 5 2.5 2.5 0 0 0 0-5M9 8a2.5 2.5 0 1 0 5 0 2.5 2.5 0 0 0-5 0"/><path d="M3 12.5h3.5v1a.5.5 0 0 1-.5.5H3.5a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5zm4 1v-1h4v1a.5.5 0 0 1-.5.5h-3a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5"/></svg>
          <span>GPU</span>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-component-card">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M11.5 2a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5v7a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0v-7a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5m2 0a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5v7a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0v-7a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5m-10 8a.5.5 0 0 0 0 1h6a.5.5 0 0 0 0-1zm0 2a.5.5 0 0 0 0 1h6a.5.5 0 0 0 0-1zM5 3a1 1 0 0 0-1 1v4a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h4a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V4a1 1 0 0 0-1-1zm0 1h4v4H5z"/><path d="M0 2a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h12a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v12a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H2a2 2 0 0 1-2-2zm2-1a1 1 0 0 0-1 1v12a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h12a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V2a1 1 0 0 0-1-1z"/></svg>
          <span>Motherboard</span>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-component-card">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M14 1a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v8a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H4.414A2 2 0 0 0 3 11.586l-2 2V2a1 1 0 0 1 1-1zM2 0a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v12.793a.5.5 0 0 0 .854.353l2.853-2.853A1 1 0 0 1 4.414 12H14a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z"/><path d="M3 3.5a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5h9a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1h-9a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5M3 6a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5h9a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1h-9A.5.5 0 0 1 3 6m0 2.5a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5h5a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1h-5a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5"/></svg>
          <span>BIOS ROM</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="beep-divider">

    <!-- Tabs Navigation -->
    <section class="beep-section">
      <h2 class="beep-heading">Beep Code Reference Tables</h2>
      <p>Select your BIOS manufacturer below. If unsure, check your motherboard manual or look for a logo on the BIOS splash screen at startup.</p>

      <div class="beep-tabs">
        <button class="beep-tab-btn active" onclick="showTab('ami')">AMI BIOS</button>
        <button class="beep-tab-btn" onclick="showTab('award')">Award BIOS</button>
        <button class="beep-tab-btn" onclick="showTab('dell')">Dell</button>
        <button class="beep-tab-btn" onclick="showTab('ibm')">IBM BIOS</button>
        <button class="beep-tab-btn" onclick="showTab('phoenix')">Phoenix BIOS</button>
      </div>

      <!-- AMI -->
      <div id="tab-ami" class="beep-tab-content active">
        <div class="beep-table-header">
          <strong>AMI (American Megatrends Inc.) BIOS Beep Codes</strong>
          <p>Common in many desktop and server motherboards. BIOS version may slightly change the meaning.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-table-wrap">
          <table class="beep-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Beep Code</th><th>Description</th><th>Component</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>1 short beep</td><td>DRAM refresh failure</td><td class="comp-badge ram">RAM</td></tr>
              <tr><td>2 short beeps</td><td>Parity circuit failure</td><td class="comp-badge ram">RAM</td></tr>
              <tr><td>3 short beeps</td><td>Base 64K RAM failure</td><td class="comp-badge ram">RAM</td></tr>
              <tr><td>4 short beeps</td><td>System timer failure</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>5 short beeps</td><td>Processor failure</td><td class="comp-badge cpu">CPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>6 short beeps</td><td>Keyboard controller Gate A20 error</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>7 short beeps</td><td>Virtual mode exception error</td><td class="comp-badge cpu">CPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>8 short beeps</td><td>Display memory Read/Write test failure</td><td class="comp-badge gpu">GPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>9 short beeps</td><td>ROM BIOS checksum failure</td><td class="comp-badge bios">BIOS</td></tr>
              <tr><td>10 short beeps</td><td>CMOS shutdown register read/write error</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>11 short beeps</td><td>Cache memory error</td><td class="comp-badge ram">RAM</td></tr>
              <tr><td>1 long, 2 short</td><td>Video card memory issue</td><td class="comp-badge gpu">GPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>1 long, 3 short</td><td>Conventional/Extended memory failure</td><td class="comp-badge ram">RAM</td></tr>
              <tr><td>1 long, 8 short</td><td>Display/Retrace test failed</td><td class="comp-badge gpu">GPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Two-tone siren</td><td>Low CPU fan speed or voltage level issue</td><td class="comp-badge cpu">CPU</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Award -->
      <div id="tab-award" class="beep-tab-content">
        <div class="beep-table-header">
          <strong>Award BIOS Beep Codes</strong>
          <p>Award BIOS (now part of Phoenix) is common in older motherboards. Most errors display a message if a screen is available.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-table-wrap">
          <table class="beep-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Beep Code</th><th>Description</th><th>Component</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>1 long, 2 short</td><td>Video error — BIOS cannot initialize the video screen</td><td class="comp-badge gpu">GPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>1 long, 3 short</td><td>Video card not detected or bad video card</td><td class="comp-badge gpu">GPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Repeating endlessly</td><td>RAM problem</td><td class="comp-badge ram">RAM</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Repeated high frequency (running)</td><td>Overheating processor</td><td class="comp-badge cpu">CPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Alternating high &amp; low</td><td>Processor issue, possibly damaged</td><td class="comp-badge cpu">CPU</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Dell -->
      <div id="tab-dell" class="beep-tab-content">
        <div class="beep-table-header">
          <strong>Dell BIOS Beep Codes</strong>
          <p>Applies to Dell desktops and laptops. Codes are consistent across most Dell models.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-table-wrap">
          <table class="beep-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Beep Code</th><th>Description</th><th>Component</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>1 beep</td><td>BIOS ROM corruption or failure</td><td class="comp-badge bios">BIOS</td></tr>
              <tr><td>2 beeps</td><td>Memory (RAM) not detected</td><td class="comp-badge ram">RAM</td></tr>
              <tr><td>3 beeps</td><td>Motherboard failure</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>4 beeps</td><td>Memory (RAM) failure</td><td class="comp-badge ram">RAM</td></tr>
              <tr><td>5 beeps</td><td>CMOS battery failure</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>6 beeps</td><td>Video card failure</td><td class="comp-badge gpu">GPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>7 beeps</td><td>Bad processor (CPU)</td><td class="comp-badge cpu">CPU</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- IBM -->
      <div id="tab-ibm" class="beep-tab-content">
        <div class="beep-table-header">
          <strong>IBM BIOS Beep Codes</strong>
          <p>General IBM BIOS codes. Varies across different IBM models and generations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-table-wrap">
          <table class="beep-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Beep Code</th><th>Description</th><th>Component</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>No beeps</td><td>No power or component not turning on</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>1 short beep</td><td>Normal POST — computer is OK</td><td class="comp-badge ok">OK</td></tr>
              <tr><td>2 short beeps</td><td>POST error — review screen for error code</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Continuous beep</td><td>No power, loose card, or short circuit</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Repeating short beep</td><td>No power, loose card, or short circuit</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>1 long, 1 short</td><td>Motherboard issue</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>1 long, 2 short</td><td>Video (Mono/CGA display circuitry) issue</td><td class="comp-badge gpu">GPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>1 long, 3 short</td><td>Video (EGA) display circuitry</td><td class="comp-badge gpu">GPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>3 long beeps</td><td>Keyboard or keyboard card error</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Keyboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>1 beep + blank display</td><td>Video display circuitry</td><td class="comp-badge gpu">GPU</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phoenix -->
      <div id="tab-phoenix" class="beep-tab-content">
        <div class="beep-table-header">
          <strong>Phoenix BIOS Beep Codes</strong>
          <p>Phoenix uses a pattern of groups separated by pauses (e.g., 1-3-1-1 means 1 beep, pause, 3 beeps, pause, 1 beep, pause, 1 beep). Only the most common codes are listed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-table-wrap">
          <table class="beep-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Beep Pattern</th><th>Description</th><th>Component</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>1-1-1-1</td><td>Unconfirmed — reseat or replace RAM chips</td><td class="comp-badge ram">RAM</td></tr>
              <tr><td>1-3-1-1</td><td>Test DRAM refresh</td><td class="comp-badge ram">RAM</td></tr>
              <tr><td>1-3-3-1</td><td>Autosize DRAM failure</td><td class="comp-badge ram">RAM</td></tr>
              <tr><td>2-1-2-1</td><td>Initialize BIOS interrupts</td><td class="comp-badge bios">BIOS</td></tr>
              <tr><td>2-1-3-2</td><td>Initialize PCI bus and devices</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>2-2-3-1</td><td>Test for unexpected interrupts</td><td class="comp-badge cpu">CPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>3-1-1-1</td><td>Disable onboard I/O ports</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>3-2-1-1</td><td>Initialize hard disk controller</td><td class="comp-badge mb">Motherboard</td></tr>
              <tr><td>4-2-1-1</td><td>Interrupt handler error</td><td class="comp-badge cpu">CPU</td></tr>
              <tr><td>4-3-2-4</td><td>Complete RAM test failure</td><td class="comp-badge ram">RAM</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Two-tone siren</td><td>Low CPU fan speed or voltage issue</td><td class="comp-badge cpu">CPU</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="beep-divider">

    <!-- Tip Section -->
    <section class="beep-section">
      <h2 class="beep-heading">Troubleshooting Tips</h2>
      <div class="beep-tips-grid">
        <div class="beep-tip-card">
          <div class="beep-tip-num">01</div>
          <h4>Identify your BIOS</h4>
          <p>Check the splash screen when the computer starts, or look at the chip label on the motherboard.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-tip-card">
          <div class="beep-tip-num">02</div>
          <h4>Count the beeps</h4>
          <p>Listen carefully and count each group of beeps. Note any pauses between groups for Phoenix codes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-tip-card">
          <div class="beep-tip-num">03</div>
          <h4>Reseat components</h4>
          <p>For RAM and GPU errors, try removing and firmly reinserting the component before replacing it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-tip-card">
          <div class="beep-tip-num">04</div>
          <h4>Check connections</h4>
          <p>Loose power cables or improperly seated cards are common causes of POST failures.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    function showTab(name) {
      document.querySelectorAll('.beep-tab-content').forEach(el => el.classList.remove('active'));
      document.querySelectorAll('.beep-tab-btn').forEach(el => el.classList.remove('active'));
      document.getElementById('tab-' + name).classList.add('active');
      event.target.classList.add('active');
    }
  </script>

</body>
</html>